entry.title: The Greatest Story is Now - Ellie Goulding - OYW 2019

media:group.media:title: The Greatest Story is Now - Ellie Goulding - OYW 2019
media:group.media:description:
Acclaimed singer and songwriter Ellie Goulding knows how to connect. She was recently recognised by the music industry having secured the most entries for any British female artist on the Billboard Hot 100 Chart this century. Overall her songs and videos secure billions of streams worldwide. She is also an environmental activist, formally acknowledged in the UN Environment Global Ambassador role she has held since 2017, but privately held as a passion since childhood. In this exclusive address to One Young World she tells the story of how she built the confidence to speak out on the climate emergency, to hang out with some of the greatest scientists working in Earth Science today and why she felt moved to ask more questions on behalf of her fans. Today, wherever possible, Ellie shares her platform and stage with activists and climate scientists. She considers them the heroes of her generation. ‚ÄòMy time on earth coincides with an extraordinary group of people facing down threat and opportunity. It would be weird if that didn‚Äôt move me!‚Äô she says. In this session Ellie represents Global Goal 13, and makes a powerful argument for us to listen and connect and tell the great stories of change and opportunity, and why sometimes the Earth needs a meme!

Slash Featuring Myles Kennedy and the Conspirators - Living the Dream Tour captures the band‚Äôs incendiary performance on their sold-out 2019 tour, in front of a rabid crowd at London‚Äôs legendary Hammersmith Apollo. This will be released on DVD+2CD, Blu-ray+2 CD, 3LP Black Vinyl, limited edition 3LP Red Vinyl, digital video and digital audio, on September 20th 2019.
Living The Dream Tour features Slash & Co. roaring through a highly charged 2-hour set of tracks from all four Slash solo albums. The set includes ‚ÄúCall of the Wild‚Äù ‚ÄúDriving Rain‚Äù, ‚ÄúBy The Sword‚Äù, ‚ÄúBack From Cali‚Äù, ‚ÄúStarlight‚Äù, ‚ÄúWorld On Fire‚Äù and ‚ÄúAnastasia‚Äù. There‚Äôs a searing live version of ‚ÄúShadow Life‚Äù, as well as ‚ÄúWe Are All Gonna Die‚Äù and ‚ÄúDoctor Alibi‚Äù, during which Myles Kennedy switches vocal duties with bassist Todd Kerns.
Slash tears up Hammersmith Apollo with staggering solos while dropping giant slabs of riffs with casual ease, delivering the essence of rock ‚Äòn‚Äô roll in this show. You could see it, hear it and feel it. ‚ÄúEvery night is chasing that magic and when it happens, it‚Äôs euphoric,‚Äù Slash states. ‚ÄúI just love it‚Ä¶London kicks ass‚Äù.
